%global debug_package %{nil}
%global packname  HDDesign
%global packver   1.1
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.1
Release:          3%{?dist}
Summary:          Sample Size Calculation for High Dimensional ClassificationStudy

License:          GPL-2
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Determine the sample size requirement to achieve the target probability of
correct classification (PCC) for studies employing high-dimensional
features.  The package implements functions to 1) determine the asymptotic
feasibility of the classification problem; 2) compute the upper bounds of
the PCC for any linear classifier; 3) estimate the PCC of three design
methods given design assumptions; 4) determine the sample size requirement
to achieve the target PCC for three design methods.

